    • Method Detail

      • dataStore

        public static RedisDataStoreBuilder dataStore()
        Returns a builder object for creating a Redis-backed data store.

        This object can be modified with RedisDataStoreBuilder methods for any desired custom Redis options. Then, pass it to Components.persistentDataStore(com.launchdarkly.client.interfaces.PersistentDataStoreFactory) and set any desired caching options. Finally, pass the result to LDConfig.Builder.dataStore(com.launchdarkly.client.FeatureStoreFactory). For example: 

        
     LDConfig config = new LDConfig.Builder()
         .dataStore(
             Components.persistentDataStore(
                 Redis.dataStore().url("redis://my-redis-host")
             ).cacheSeconds(15)
         )
         .build();
        Returns:
        a data store configuration object
